The paper proposes a technique for enabling chatbots to continuously learn new knowledge during conversations, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques used to model the task as an open-world knowledge base completion problem. The proposed technique involves interactive learning and inference, which can be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
